& [RGBSemanticEncodingTrailingChecksum065] is the trailing checksum for the prior RGB encoding frame
  + [reviewed_focus] is SOP RGB semantic encoding
  + [prior_inside] is RGB primitive basis, RGB mixture roles, SOP-to-RGB encode pass, RGB-to-SOP decode pass, and complex relationship color encoding
  + [observed_fault] is red_axis carried impulse, claim, action, transformation pressure, and output pressure, which blurred attention delineation with mutation and operation semantics
  + [corrected_boundary] is RGB axes encode attention/delineation only: inside attention, boundary delineation, and outside residual/periphery
  + [hot_zone] is the distinction between color as a delineation map and transform algebra as the mutation/operator surface
  + [warm_zone] is complex relationships still need color-point and relation-edge structures, but the edge color should encode the relation's inside, boundary, and outside, not relation mutation force
  + [latent_depth] is future optical programs may overlay operations as separate transform expressions over delineated RGB frames
  + [correction] is update SOPRGBSemanticEncoding so mutation, action, transformation, and output pressure are not primitive RGB axis meanings
  + [next_focus_candidate] is RGB attention delineation correction
  + [balance_state] is restored when delineation and operation layers remain orthogonal

  = must: treat this checksum as backward-facing correction of the previous commit
  = must: keep mutation and operation semantics in SOPOpticalTransformAlgebra or another explicit operation layer
  - outside: direct operation encoding in RGB primitives, color-only proof, and untraced mutation

